SAPS spokesperson, Brenda Muridili speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Protest action has begun in Diepsloot in Johannesburg. A call for a total shutdown was made on several social media platforms. Organisers say residents want an end to crime and violence in the area. READ: Mass COVID-19 testing drive held in Diepsloot They are demanding more police visibility and want to speak to Police Minister, Bheki Cele. Organisers say the area will be shut down for two days. Watch the video above for more details on this story